comment: Johnson (BOS) cleanly knocks away the pass intended for Mahinmi (IND).
Mahinmi (IND) moves his pivot foot. Because of the defensive pressure by Johnson (BOS), the official is watching the defender to look for any illegal contact and does not pick up the pivot foot.
Smart (BOS) cleanly strips the ball from Miles (IND).
Mahinmi (IND) sets the screen on Crowder (BOS) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
RHH shows that Smart (BOS) maintains legal guarding position and Crowder (BOS) cleanly strips the ball from George (IND).
LHH shows that Hill (IND) maintains legal guarding position as he defends Thomas' (BOS) driving layup attempt. Any contact on the play is created by Thomas.
Johnson (BOS) legally contests Miles' (IND) jump shot attempt.
After Thomas (BOS) secures the loose ball and begins to turn upcourt, George (IND) makes contact with him and affects his RSBQ.
Miles (IND) reaches in for the steal and makes contact with Thomas (BOS).
